# Vue — Quasar standard components

When building UI in `apps/web/`:

- Prefer **Quasar built-ins** over custom implementations:
  - Tables → `q-table` (not hand-rolled `<table>`)
  - Forms → `q-form` + `q-input` + `q-btn`
  - File upload → `q-uploader`
  - Dialogs → `useQuasar().dialog(...)` or `q-dialog`
  - Notifications → `useQuasar().notify(...)`
  - Loading states → `q-spinner` or `q-inner-loading`
- Do not use raw hex color literals. Use Quasar CSS variables (`$primary`, `$positive`, etc.) or utility classes (`text-primary`, `bg-grey-2`).
- Layout: `q-layout` + `q-page-container` + `q-page` — do not invent custom wrappers for the top-level shell.
